<h3>Submit OS News</h3>

Please use HTML to represent the links in your submission. We are also beta-testing our new submission API.

If you would like to submit an entire original article for publication, please read the aformentioned OSNews Style Guide thoroughly before you do so. Compliance with the Style Guide greatly increases the chances of your article being accepted without a hitch. 

	<p>OSNews.com is always interested to hear from you the latest news on a vast range of Operating Systems and related technlogies, from the well-known mainstream OSes, down to small, mobile, amateur, personal or embedded ones.</p>
	<p>Please <b>use HTML</b> to represent the links in your submission. For more detailed information on how to best format your news submissions, please refer to our <a href="http://www.osnews.com/files/osnews_style_guide.pdf">Style Guide</a> [.pdf].  You can also use our <a href="/api/">our submission API</a>.</p>
	
	<p>If you instead would like to submit an entire original article for publication, please read the aformentioned OSNews Style Guide thoroughly before you do so. Compliance with the Style Guide greatly increases the chances of your article being accepted. 
<p>Please <b>make sure</b> the news you are submitting has not already been posted. Below is a list of the currently <b>pending submissions</b> on osnews.com:<br />
- <i>Playing Extreme Games like Battlefield 4 is now Possible in Budget PC</i><br />
- <i>Google and the NSA: Who’s holding the ‘shit-bag’ now?</i><br />
- <i>Open Source Meets Education - Outstanding Linux Applications</i><br />
- <i>Patch 5.4 Guide : Timeless Isle</i><br />
